1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to state government; enacting the
Freedmen of Oklahoma Act; providing for forfeiture of
8 certain cooperative agreements and contracts by
Indian tribes under certain circumstances; providing
9 for forfeiture of funds by Indian tribes under
certain circumstances; providing that the Attorney
10 General shall bring certain court proceedings;
creating the Freedmen of Oklahoma Commission;
11 providing duties; providing for membership of
Commission; providing for codification; and providing
12 an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1227.1 of Title 74, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Freedmen of
20 Oklahoma Act".
21 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1227.2 of Title 74, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 11770 Page 1
1 A. Federally recognized Indian tribes in the State of Oklahoma
2 that fail to grant citizenship rights to freedmen descendants,
3 pursuant to their respective treaties, shall:
4 1. Forfeit all cooperative agreements and contracts with the
5 State of Oklahoma. Provided, however, that any intergovernmental
6 cooperative agreements entered into pursuant to subsection D of
7 Section 1221 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall be excluded
8 from forfeiture; and
9 2. Forfeit all funds received or expended by the State of
10 Oklahoma for the benefit of the tribe, except as may be required by
11 law.
12 B. The Office of the Attorney General shall bring court
13 proceedings in the proper courts to enforce this act.
14 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1227.3 of Title 74, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. There is hereby created the Freedmen of Oklahoma Commission
18 to enforce the rights defined in Section 2 of this act to study the
19 economic and social impacts of the 1866 treaties and their ongoing
20 implementation, including, but not limited to, tribal citizenship of
21 and benefits for freedmen and their descendants.
22 B. The Commission shall be comprised of fifteen (15) members to
23 be appointed as follows:
24 1. Five members by the Governor;
Req. No. 11770 Page 2
1 2. Five members by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
2 Representatives; and
3 3. Five members by the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma
4 State Senate.
5 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
